GRAMMAR

Word Formation:

Words are often formed through compounding, as well as, less often through derivation by affixes.

Word Order:

The standard word order is SOV

Nouns:

Nouns can be inflected for 2 numbers, Dual and Plural

To Dualize, add the prefix of Tja- or if the word starts with a Vowel Tj-
To Pluralize, add a prefix of Ke- or if the word starts with a Vowel Ket-

Possesives are formed using the possive particle nge, ie. Maro nge te (Lit, Cat POSS me), trans. My Cat

Verbs:

verbs are not conjugated, and uses particles or suffixes for tense etc.
verbs are also not 'to verb' but just the concept of the verb

Past tense is prefixed Ke-
Hodiernal Past is prefixed with Ka-
Future tense is prefixed with Tange-
Hodiernal future is prefixed with Te-


Senuyakh has active and passive voices as particles, ie Ayatokh ketameng mang (food past-eat passive) or Te ayatokh ketameng mek (SFPPP food past-eat active)
